{
  "enabled": true,
  "name": "TDD — Run Tests After Code Changes",
  "description": "Enforces TDD workflow: after editing Python source or test files, run the relevant tests immediately. Tests must be written BEFORE implementation (Red-Green-Refactor).",
  "version": "1",
  "when": {
    "type": "fileEdited",
    "patterns": [
      "**/src/**/*.py",
      "**/tests/**/*.py"
    ]
  },
  "then": {
    "type": "askAgent",
    "prompt": "You just edited a Python file. Follow the TDD workflow:\n\n1. If you wrote a TEST file: run it now with `uv run pytest <test_file>::<test_name> -v` — it should FAIL (RED). If it passes, you wrote the implementation first — that violates TDD.\n\n2. If you wrote a SOURCE file: run the corresponding test with `uv run pytest tests/unit/ -v --tb=short` — it should now PASS (GREEN). If it fails, fix it NOW before writing more code.\n\n3. NEVER skip running tests. NEVER write more implementation without a failing test first.\n\nRun the tests in the correct repo directory using cwd."
  }
}
